2025-05-30 00:26:00,569 - copilot_service - INFO - Question: What is the Aggregate Method in Amortized Analysis?
2025-05-30 00:26:00,569 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method determines an upper bound on the total cost of a sequence of n operations, then divides by n to get the amortized cost per operation. It ensures that the total cost is distributed evenly across all operations.
2025-05-30 00:26:00,570 - copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
