2025-05-30 00:30:42,261 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method determines an upper bound on the total cost of a sequence of n operations, then divides by n to get the amortized cost per operation. It ensures the average cost is within bounds without considering individual operation costs.
