2025-05-30 00:38:17,705 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Textual Analysis involves examining the structure, language, and style of a text to identify patterns, themes, and literary devices. This concept encourages learners to break down a text into its components, analyze their relationships, and draw insights from the author's craft.
