2025-05-30 00:38:17,707 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: Critical Evaluation entails assessing the credibility, accuracy, and relevance of a text's content, arguments, and sources. This concept promotes the development of critical thinking skills, enabling learners to form well-informed opinions, identify biases, and distinguish between fact and opinion.
