2025-05-30 00:39:41,535 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method determines an upper bound T(n) on the total cost of a sequence of n operations. The amortized cost per operation is then calculated as T(n)/n, providing an average cost per operation.
2025-05-30 00:39:41,535 - copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-05-30 00:39:41,536 - copilot_service - INFO - 
