2025-05-30 00:43:33,473 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A technique in amortized analysis that uses a potential function to assign amortized costs based on the state of the data structure. The potential function measures the 
2025-05-30 00:43:33,474 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Augmented Stack: The potential method can be applied to analyze stack operations by defining a potential function based on the number of elements in the stack. This ensures that the amortized cost of push, pop, and multipop operations remains O(1).
2025-05-30 00:43:33,474 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A study by Sleator and Tarjan (2010) extended the potential method to analyze splay trees, a self-adjusting binary search tree, providing a deeper understanding of how potential functions can model the behavior of dynamic data structures (Sleator & Tarjan, 2010).
