2025-05-30 00:58:50,183 - copilot_service - INFO - Answer: The Aggregate Method first analyzes the entire sequence and then calculates the amortized cost per operation, while the Accounting Method first assigns amortized costs per operation and then computes the total cost of the sequence, providing the per-operation cost.
