Concept 8:
2025-05-30 01:01:07,123 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Vertex Cover Problem
2025-05-30 01:01:07,123 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Given an undirected graph, find the smallest subset of vertices such that every edge in the graph is incident to at least one vertex in the subset.
2025-05-30 01:01:07,124 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Vertex cover problems arise in wireless sensor networks, where the goal is to select the minimum number of sensors to cover all areas of interest.
2025-05-30 01:01:07,125 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Recent work by [Chaudhary and Garg, 2020](https://doi.org/10.1145/3387902.3392608) presented a 2-approximation algorithm for the vertex cover problem with improved running time, making it more practical for large-scale graphs.
