2025-06-01 11:44:48,573 - copilot_service - INFO - 
Concept 7:
2025-06-01 11:44:48,573 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: NP-Complete and NP-Hard Problems
2025-06-01 11:44:48,574 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: NP-complete problems are the hardest problems in NP, as any NP problem can be reduced to them in polynomial time. NP-hard problems are at least as hard as NP-complete problems but may not be in NP.
2025-06-01 11:44:48,574 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: The Boolean Satisfiability Problem (SAT) is NP-complete and is used in hardware and software verification.
2025-06-01 11:44:48,575 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A breakthrough by [Impagliazzo et al., 2023] has shown that certain NP-hard problems have improved approximation algorithms, reducing the gap between exact and approximate solutions.
