2025-06-01 11:44:48,577 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Algorithms that find near-optimal solutions to optimization problems in polynomial time, often used when exact solutions are computationally infeasible.
2025-06-01 11:44:48,577 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Approximation algorithms are used in routing and scheduling problems, such as the Vehicle Routing Problem, to find efficient routes for delivery vehicles.
2025-06-01 11:44:48,578 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Research by [Vazirani, 2022] has introduced new approximation algorithms for the Knapsack Problem with improved performance guarantees, making them more practical for real-world applications.
