2025-06-01 11:44:48,580 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Given an undirected graph, find the smallest subset of vertices such that every edge is incident to at least one vertex in the subset.
2025-06-01 11:44:48,580 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Vertex cover problems arise in network design, where the goal is to place the minimum number of monitors to cover all connections.
