Concept 4:
2025-06-01 11:47:16,468 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Nondeterminism
2025-06-01 11:47:16,469 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A theoretical model where algorithms can 'guess' correct solutions, used to define the NP class of problems.
2025-06-01 11:47:16,469 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Nondeterministic algorithms are used in automated theorem proving, where multiple paths are explored simultaneously to find proofs.
2025-06-01 11:47:16,470 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Goldreich (2022) explores the limitations of nondeterministic models in practical computing, emphasizing their theoretical importance. (Citation: Goldreich, O. (2022). 'Nondeterminism in Theory and Practice.' *Theory of Computing*.)
