2025-06-01 11:55:42,464 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A class of decision problems for which no efficient (polynomial-time) solution is known, but solutions can be verified quickly. These problems are the hardest in the NP class.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,466 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Scheduling problems, such as the Job Shop Scheduling Problem, where tasks need to be assigned to machines with minimal idle time.
