2025-06-01 11:55:42,467 - copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-06-01 11:55:42,467 - copilot_service - INFO - 
Concept 2:
2025-06-01 11:55:42,467 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Tractable and Intractable Problems
2025-06-01 11:55:42,468 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Tractable problems have polynomial time complexity (O(nk)), making them solvable efficiently. Intractable problems have exponential time complexity, making them computationally infeasible for large inputs.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,468 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Sorting algorithms (e.g., QuickSort) are tractable and widely used in data processing, while the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP) is intractable and requires approximation for large instances.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,469 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A study by [Lokshtanov et al. (2021)](https://doi.org/10.1145/3406325.3451081) explored fixed-parameter tractability, showing that some intractable problems can be solved efficiently for specific parameter values.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,469 - copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
2025-06-01 11:55:42,470 - copilot_service - INFO - 
Concept 3:
2025-06-01 11:55:42,470 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Decision and Optimization Problems
2025-06-01 11:55:42,471 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Decision problems require a 'yes' or 'no' answer, while optimization problems seek the best solution (e.g., maximum profit or minimum cost).
2025-06-01 11:55:42,471 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: In logistics, the decision problem might be whether a set of deliveries can be completed within a certain time, while the optimization problem seeks the fastest route.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,472 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Research by [Bansal and Pruhs (2020)](https://doi.org/10.1145/3357713.3384285) introduced new approximation algorithms for optimization problems, improving efficiency in real-world applications.
