Concept 6:
2025-06-01 11:55:42,478 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Polynomial Reduction
2025-06-01 11:55:42,479 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A method of transforming one problem (L1) into another (L2) such that the solution to L2 provides a solution to L1. The transformation must be computable in polynomial time.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,479 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Reducing the Hamiltonian Cycle Problem to the Traveling Salesman Problem to leverage existing TSP algorithms.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,480 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A study by [Cygan et al. (2020)](https://doi.org/10.1145/3357713.3384320) introduced new reduction techniques for graph problems, improving efficiency in algorithm design.
