Concept 7:
2025-06-01 11:55:42,481 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: NP-Complete and NP-Hard Problems
2025-06-01 11:55:42,481 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: NP-Complete problems are the hardest in NP, as any NP problem can be reduced to them in polynomial time. NP-Hard problems are at least as hard as NP-Complete problems but may not be in NP.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,482 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: The Boolean Satisfiability Problem (SAT) is NP-Complete and used in hardware verification and AI planning.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,482 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Research by [Khanna et al. (2022)](https://doi.org/10.1145/3498700.3501763) explored the boundaries of NP-Hardness, identifying new problems that are NP-Hard but not NP-Complete.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,483 - copilot_service - INFO - --------------------------------------------------
