2025-06-01 11:55:42,484 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Algorithms that find near-optimal solutions to optimization problems in polynomial time, often used when exact solutions are computationally infeasible.
2025-06-01 11:55:42,485 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Approximation algorithms for the Vertex Cover Problem are used in network design to minimize the number of servers needed.
