2025-06-01 12:59:15,266 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: P-class includes decision problems solvable in polynomial time by deterministic algorithms. NP-class includes problems solvable in polynomial time by nondeterministic algorithms or problems whose solutions can be verified in polynomial time.
2025-06-01 12:59:15,267 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Integer Factorization: Determining if a number is prime (in P) vs. finding its prime factors (believed to be outside P but in NP). This has direct applications in cryptography, particularly in RSA encryption.
