Concept 3:
2025-06-01 14:05:54,555 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Polynomial Reduction
2025-06-01 14:05:54,555 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A transformation of one problem (L1) into another (L2) such that the solution to L2 can be used to solve L1 in polynomial time.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,556 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Used in compiler optimization, where complex code is reduced to simpler problems that can be optimized more easily.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,556 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Research by [Cygan et al., 2021] developed a new framework for polynomial reductions that improves the efficiency of solving NP-hard problems.
