Concept 5:
2025-06-01 14:05:54,560 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: NP-Hard
2025-06-01 14:05:54,560 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A class of problems that are at least as hard as the hardest problems in NP, but not necessarily in NP themselves.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,560 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Used in game theory to model complex strategic interactions where finding an optimal solution is computationally infeasible.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,562 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Research by [Chen et al., 2022] explored the relationship between NP-hard problems and machine learning, suggesting new approaches to approximate solutions.
