2025-06-01 14:05:54,563 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: Algorithms that find near-optimal solutions to optimization problems in polynomial time, often used when exact solutions are computationally expensive.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,564 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Used in resource allocation problems, such as allocating bandwidth in telecommunications networks.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,564 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A study by [Vazirani, 2023] introduced a new approximation algorithm for the Knapsack problem that achieves a better approximation ratio than previous methods.
