2025-06-01 14:05:54,567 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: The problem of finding the smallest subset of vertices in a graph such that every edge is incident to at least one vertex in the subset.
2025-06-01 14:05:54,567 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Used in network design to identify critical nodes that ensure all connections are monitored or controlled.
