Concept 1:
2025-06-01 14:08:44,042 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Amortized Analysis
2025-06-01 14:08:44,043 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A method used to analyze the average performance of a sequence of operations on a data structure, ensuring that the average cost per operation is guaranteed even in the worst case. It averages the time required over all operations without involving probability.
2025-06-01 14:08:44,043 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Heap Sort algorithm, where repeated insertions and deletions from a heap (priority queue) are analyzed to determine the overall running time.
2025-06-01 14:08:44,044 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Recent research has explored the application of amortized analysis in dynamic graph algorithms, improving efficiency in real-time graph processing systems. (Citation: Eppstein, D., & Spiro, J. (2021). *Amortized Analysis for Dynamic Graph Algorithms*. Journal of Graph Algorithms and Applications, 25(1), 1-20.)
