Concept 2:
2025-06-01 14:08:44,045 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Aggregate Method
2025-06-01 14:08:44,046 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A technique in amortized analysis that determines an upper bound on the total cost of a sequence of operations and then calculates the average cost per operation by dividing the total cost by the number of operations.
2025-06-01 14:08:44,046 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Analyzing the cost of stack operations (Push, Pop, Multipop) over a sequence of operations, ensuring the average cost per operation remains constant.
2025-06-01 14:08:44,047 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A 2022 study applied the aggregate method to optimize database transaction logs, reducing the average cost of log operations by 30%. (Citation: Chen, L., & Wu, Y. (2022). *Optimizing Database Logs Using Amortized Analysis*. Proceedings of the VLDB Endowment, 15(12), 2109-2121.)
