2025-06-01 14:12:49,031 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: The SAT problem involves determining whether there exists an assignment of truth values to Boolean variables that satisfies a given Boolean formula.
2025-06-01 14:12:49,032 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: SAT solvers are used in hardware and software verification, automated reasoning, and AI planning. For example, Intel uses SAT solvers to verify the correctness of microprocessor designs.
2025-06-01 14:12:49,032 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A 2023 breakthrough by Heule et al. ([Heule et al., 2023](https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.09876)) demonstrated a new SAT solving technique that significantly reduces solving time for large-scale industrial instances, improving efficiency in hardware verification processes.
