2025-06-01 14:12:49,034 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: The Independent Set Problem seeks to find the largest set of vertices in a graph such that no two vertices in the set are adjacent.
2025-06-01 14:12:49,035 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: This problem has applications in scheduling, where tasks (vertices) cannot be scheduled simultaneously if they conflict (adjacent edges). For example, assigning time slots to lectures in a university timetable.
