2025-06-03 23:09:33,016 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: NP-Completeness
2025-06-03 23:09:33,016 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A problem is NP-complete if it is in NP (solutions can be verified in polynomial time) and every other NP problem can be reduced to it in polynomial time.
2025-06-03 23:09:33,017 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: NP-completeness is crucial in cryptography. For example, the RSA encryption system relies on the difficulty of factoring large numbers, a problem believed to be NP-complete.
2025-06-03 23:09:33,017 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Recent research has explored the relationship between NP-completeness and quantum computing. A study by Bravyi et al. (2020) investigates how quantum algorithms might impact the complexity of NP-complete problems (Bravyi, Gosset, & König, 2020).
