2025-06-03 23:09:33,022 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: The Halting Problem asks whether, given a program and an input, the program will eventually halt (terminate) when run with that input. It is known to be undecidable.
2025-06-03 23:09:33,023 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: The Halting Problem is fundamental in software verification and testing. Tools like static analyzers attempt to predict program behavior, but they cannot solve the Halting Problem in general.
