2025-06-03 23:09:33,024 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: The Independent Set Problem seeks to find the largest set of vertices in a graph such that no two vertices in the set are adjacent.
2025-06-03 23:09:33,024 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: The Independent Set Problem is used in scheduling and resource allocation. For example, it can model assigning tasks to processors without conflicts.
2025-06-03 23:09:33,024 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: Recent research by Chen et al. (2021) introduces a new approximation algorithm for the Independent Set Problem, improving upon previous bounds (Chen, Kanj, & Xia, 2021).
