2025-06-03 23:12:20,817 - copilot_service - INFO - 
Concept 2:
2025-06-03 23:12:20,817 - copilot_service - INFO - Name: Fractional Knapsack Problem
2025-06-03 23:12:20,818 - copilot_service - INFO - Definition: A variation of the classic knapsack problem where items can be divided into fractions, allowing for partial selection of items to maximize total value without exceeding the knapsack's capacity.
2025-06-03 23:12:20,819 - copilot_service - INFO - Application: Resource allocation in cloud computing. Cloud providers can allocate fractional resources (e.g., CPU, memory) to virtual machines based on demand, maximizing resource utilization and revenue.
2025-06-03 23:12:20,819 - copilot_service - INFO - Insight: A 2022 paper by Zhang et al. (https://doi.org/10.1145/3514088.3514109) proposed a novel greedy algorithm for the fractional knapsack problem with dynamic item values, achieving near-optimal solutions in polynomial time.
